  "prompt": "How do I become a sub inspector in delhi police after graduation?",
  "response": "To become a Sub Inspector (SI) in the Delhi Police after graduation, you need to follow a process that typically involves meeting eligibility criteria, passing examinations, and completing training. Here\u2019s a step-by-step guide:\n\n1. **Ensure Eligibility**: \n   - **Educational Qualification**: You must have a bachelor\u2019s degree from a recognized university or equivalent.\n   - **Age Limit**: Generally, candidates must be between 20 and 25 years of age. There are age relaxations for candidates belonging to reserved categories, such as SC, ST, and OBC.\n   - **Physical Standards**: You must meet certain physical standards, which vary slightly for male and female candidates.\n\n2. **Notification and Application**:\n   - Keep an eye on notifications released by the Staff Selection Commission (SSC) or the Delhi Police department regarding SI recruitment. The recruitment for Sub-Inspectors in Delhi Police is often part of the SSC CPO (Central Police Organization) Examination.\n   - Once the notification is out, fill out the application form online through the official SSC website.\n\n3. **Preparation and Written Examination**:\n   - **Paper I (Objective Type)**: This is the first stage of the examination, usually covering topics such as General Knowledge and General Awareness, Quantitative Aptitude, English Comprehension, and Reasoning.\n   - **Physical Endurance Test (PET)/Physical Standard Test (PST)**: Candidates who qualify in Paper I are required to undergo PET/PST.\n   - **Paper II (English Language & Comprehension)**: Candidates who clear the PET/PST have to appear for this exam, which tests English language proficiency.\n   - It\u2019s important to refer to the latest examination pattern and syllabus provided in the official notifications for preparation.\n\n4. **Medical Examination and Document Verification**:\n   - Successful candidates must undergo a medical examination to ensure they meet the health standards required for the role.\n   - You will also need to present original documents for verification.\n\n5. **Final Selection and Training**:\n   - Candidates who clear all the stages are placed in the merit list based on their performance in Paper I, Paper II, and PET/PST.\n   - Once selected, you must undergo training at a police training school or academy designated by the Delhi Police.\n\n6. **Continuous Preparation**:\n   - Since the selection process is competitive, it\u2019s advisable to start preparing early. You can use various resources like books, online courses, and coaching centers specializing in competitive examination preparation to enhance your chances of success.\n\nMake sure to regularly check the official SSC and Delhi Police websites and newspapers for updates on recruitment notifications and exam-related announcements.",
